Then we scale it down to a box size.
Today, you can put it on a PCI card and plug it into an ordinary computer.
This is the world's fastest, truly random number generator.
It can generate 1 billion random numbers per second by measuring quantum effects.
Today it is widely used around the world to improve security for cloud service providers, banks and government agencies.
(Applause.) But even with true random number generators, we have a second big cybersecurity threat: the secure delivery of secret keys.
