Let's assume that Dr. Noe wants to get the password.
Luckily, when Dr. Noh tries to intercept this quantum key, he leaves an electronic fingerprint that James and you can detect.
The intercepted key will be invalid.
The remaining keys provide strong protection for the data.
Because this security mechanism is based on fundamental principles of physics, it's impossible for a quantum computer, or any supercomputer of the future, to crack it.
